bib.title: Searching for resonances in the unbound 6Be nucleusby using a radioactive 7Be beam

free_txt: Sungkyunkwan University, Suwon
Experiment performed at the Oak Ridge
National Laboratory's Holifield Radioactive Ion Beam
Facility.
Compiled by S.H.
Recoiling tritons were detected by
using a large-area silicon detector array SIDAR. The
SIDAR was configured with 100 mu-m detectors dE
backed by 500 mu-m E detectors. Additional layer of
detectors (veto-detectors, 300 mu-m thick) was
placed behind the E detectors to detect the 3He
particles punching through the E detectors and to
exclude those particles from the dE-E plot.
